* File: externalcall.lpi
* Author: Manfred Jeusfeld, Tilburg University
* Date: 7-Aug-2001
*-------------------------------------------------
* Copy this file into the database directory that has been pre-loaded
* with the model externalcall.sml
*}

{* The answer format generator passes a pointer to a string
buffer (a special memory structure in CB to handle strings)
as first argument to the external predicate. All other items
 expects a substring to be a list
of atoms. Hence, we generate a list that contains just a single
atom which is the current time.
The format of the current time is a bit strange. It is used
here to demonstrate the call of external predicates.
Knowledge of ConceptBase source code and MasterProlog
is required to use this feature.
*}

anExternalPredicate(_buf,_a,_b) :-
  pc_atomconcat$PrologCompatibility(_a,_b,_c),
  appendBuffer$ExternalCodeLoader(_buf,_c),
  !.



